Seven suspects arrested in connection with farm attacks were all remanded custody at Lebowakgomo Magistrate Court in Limpopo on Thursday.Mhlabane Bheki, Mbuyane Mpoh Paul, Nkosi Dumisane, Shabane Ntando, Mlazi Sfiso, Bhokodisa vision and Phiri Nhlanhla Willis were all arrested in connection to farm attacks.It is alleged that in August an unknown number of suspects attacked an elderly couple in their house at the Immerpan Farm near Zebediela on the outskirts of Mokopane.The bodies of Pieter van Zyl (69) and his wife Mathilda van Zyl were discovered the next day with multiple gunshot wounds with their hands tied.Yesterday, four suspects attacked the farmer and killing his wife at the TNT farm just outside Bela Bela. It is alleged that four suspects, two wearing balaclavas and hand gloves arrived at this farm, pointed the domestic worker with firearms and instructed her to the owner s house.Provincial Police spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe said a manhunt have been launched for a group of armed suspects who wounded a farmer and fatally killed his wife. in Limpopo.The seven will appear in court on Friday for formal bail application and for further Police investigations.TNA Reporter &nbsp;